## Architecture

ZEDD uses a modern, distributed architecture designed for maximum reliability and throughput.

![System Architecture](FlowChart.png)

> Solid arrows represent direct data/request flow. Dotted arrows represent asynchronous notification and delivery callbacks.

| Layer | Description |
|---|---|
| **Client Layer** | Entry point for Users & Developers via Web Dashboard or Public API |
| **Backend Infrastructure** | Core application logic connected to a PostgreSQL database |
| **Processing Pipeline** | Task Queue (Celery/Redis) → Worker Cluster → AI Processing Engine |
| **Storage & Delivery** | Object Storage for processed assets + Notification System for async callbacks |

---

## Technology Stack

| Component | Technology |
|---|---|
| **Backend** | Python — Flask & FastAPI |
| **Task Queue** | Celery with Redis as the message broker |
| **Database** | PostgreSQL — multi-tenant relational schema |
| **AI Frameworks** | PyTorch and specialized computer vision libraries |
| **DevOps** | Containerized deployment with Nginx for reverse proxying |
| **Integrations** | Enterprise-grade payment processing & secure webhook delivery |

